1. About this .MOD.

I've been attempting to make use of the .MOD format in my compositions
for some time now, without success.  The .MOD format seems to lend itself
to creating music with driving beats, ala techno, etc.

This .MOD is my first near-success at creating a piece of ostensibly
"minimal" or "reductivist" music.  This particular .MOD seems much
more interesting to most listeners when wearing headphones - there are
many subtleties in the way the sounds overlap.

The piece is about 8 minutes long, and only uses three different samples.

It was composed with OctaMED v5.  I have tried converting it to "standard"
tracker formats, for cross-platform compatability, with no luck.  Some of
the important nuances of the piece are lost in the translation.

OctaMED Player is included in this archive.

